to
the
real
world:
for
Nunnely
Wood
in
June
she
saw
her
narrow
chamber;
for
the
songs
of
birds
in
alleys
she
heard
the
rain
on
her
casement;
for
the
sigh
of
the
south
wind
came
the
sob
of
the
mournful
east;
and
for
Moore's
manly
companionship
she
had
the
thin
